name: Hyatt Centric Sacramento Downtown
description:
Located conveniently in Sacramento, Hyatt Centric Sacramento Downtown has air-conditioned rooms, a fitness center, free WiFi and a shared lounge. This 4-star hotel offers room service and a 24-hour front desk. The hotel has a terrace and city views, and guests can enjoy a meal at the restaurant or a drink at the bar.
At the hotel, the rooms come with a closet, a flat-screen TV, a private bathroom, bed linen and towels.
Guests at Hyatt Centric Sacramento Downtown can enjoy an à la carte or an American breakfast.
Popular points of interest near the accommodation include California Capitol Building, Sacramento Valley Amtrak Station and Crocker Art Museum. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 9.3 miles from Hyatt Centric Sacramento Downtown.

name: Courtyard Sacramento Airport Natomas
description:
Just one mile from the Sacramento River, this hotel offers free airport shuttle service to Sacramento International Airport, a 10 miles drive.  A restaurant, pool and gym are on site.
The spacious rooms at Courtyard Sacramento Airport Natomas feature white cotton linens and cable TV.  Each bathroom is stocked with free Neutrogena bathroom amenities.
Breakfast, dinner and cocktails are served at Courtyard Sacramento Airport’s restaurant, The Bistro.  The hotel’s Marketplace shop stocks beverages and light snacks.
Courtyard Sacramento features an outdoor terrace, swimming pool and whirlpool.  Guests also have access to an on-site ATM and business center.

userReviews.title: All we wanted: Pleasant, clean and safe stay for a short overnight stay
userReviews.positive: Great for the money: This was above budget, but not even close to high-end. Thus, great for us. We've stayed in the Sacramento area many times, and have mostly gone super-budget. Some places we liked in the past have upgraded and are more expensive than we liked for the neighborhood. And, we weren't in the mood for going the route of Motel 6-double-bed, freeway-side, sketch-neighborhood. The Courtyard, being in a business park, in the slow period over the holidays seemed like a good compromise. It was slightly more money, but we got options for either a King bed and sofabed or double queen beds and a bigger upgrade in comfort and location. Some reviews I read here complain about the need for an upgrade; that the property seems old. Not to us, at this point in time. Room 207 was attractive, clean, comfortable, with plenty of outlets for our devices, easy-to-log-on WiFi. The unit was easy to access because of the automated doors all around the property, and our keys allowed us in after hours. There were both wide stairways and elevator service, which allowed us choice and quick pathways to our room. Great value and comfort for the money.
userReviews.negative: The parking fee. The website needs to post the parking fee of $7.50 clearly so customers can properly make a decision about staying at the property. I'm not used to paying for parking, but through the reviews on the third-party site, I was at least able to anticipate and factor this into my decision. The parking lot was ample and it was easy to access the building no matter where we parked, so that offset the parking fee for me. Security did not appear to be a problem, but we tend to not keep things in the car overnight when traveling.
userReviews.room: Queen Room with Two Queen Beds

name: Tapestry By Hilton The Fort Sutter Hotel Sacramento, Ca
description:
Located 19 miles from University of California, Davis, Tapestry By Hilton The Fort Sutter Hotel Sacramento, Ca offers 3-star accommodations in Sacramento and has a bar. Featuring a fitness center, the 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with a private bathroom. The property has room service, a 24-hour front desk and luggage storage for guests.
Rooms include a flat-screen TV, and certain accommodations at the hotel have a city view.
Breakfast is available each morning, and includes à la carte, continental and American options. At Tapestry By Hilton The Fort Sutter Hotel Sacramento, Ca you'll find a restaurant serving American cuisine. Vegetarian, vegan and dairy-free options can also be requested.
California State Capitol and Museum is 1.4 miles from the accommodation, while Sacramento Convention Center is 1.5 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 11 miles from Tapestry By Hilton The Fort Sutter Hotel Sacramento, Ca.

A very nice, modern, and clean hotel in a great downtown location. The two rooms we booked were in like new condition... no weird hotel smells, everything was clean, and everything worked. The bathrooms were also very nice with good lighting and, according to my wife, quality soaps and haircare products; however, the shower was quite narrow due to the grab bar that protruded from the shower wall.  
Parking is in a public parking structure next to the hotel. We paid $18 for each night, but because it's public, there are no in-and-out privileges. 
When we visit Sacramento in the future, this hotel will definitely be top on our list.
userReviews.negative:
Housekeeping, to our dismay, was available only upon request. The hotel upon check-in does not inform you of this fact; rather, they have placed a small sticker on the inside of the room's door... not exactly in your line of sight unless you're an exceptionally short person. Unless you're receiving an absolutely rock-bottom nightly rate, daily housekeeping should be standard at this price point. COVID should no longer be used as an excuse!
Our takeaway: Request daily housekeeping at check-in.

name: Hyatt House Sacramento-Midtown
description:
Located in Sacramento, 19 miles from University of California, Davis, Hyatt House Sacramento-Midtown has accommodations with a shared lounge, private parking, a restaurant and a bar. Located around 1.3 miles from California State Capitol and Museum, the hotel with free WiFi is also 1.1 miles away from Sacramento Convention Center. The property provides a 24-hour front desk and a business center for guests.
At the hotel, rooms come with a desk. Complete with a private bathroom equipped with free toiletries, all rooms at Hyatt House Sacramento-Midtown have a flat-screen TV and air conditioning, and selected rooms also offer a balcony. At the accommodation all rooms include bed linen and towels.
Hyatt House Sacramento-Midtown offers a buffet or American breakfast.
California Capitol Building is 1.7 miles from the hotel, while Sacramento Valley Amtrak Station is 2.2 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 11 miles from Hyatt House Sacramento-Midtown.

American River Bike Trail is located adjacent to the hotel. The California State Railroad Museum, Crocker Museum and Old Sacramento are within 1 mi of La Quinta Inn Sacramento Downtown.

description:
This Sacramento motel is within 5 minutes’ drive of the Sacramento Convention Center and California State Capitol Museum. Cable TV with film channels is included in all rooms.
Each air-conditioned room at Motel 6 Sacramento- Old Sacramento North features an private bathroom. All rooms include colorful decor and light wood furnishings.
A 24-hour reception is offered at Old Sacramento North - Sacramento Motel 6. Guests can enjoy an outdoor terrace by the pool. Fax and photocopying services are available.
Sacramento International Airport is 15 minutes’ drive away. Adjacent to the Motel 6 Sacramento is the Discovery Museum, shops and cafes.

name: Governors Inn Hotel Sacramento
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Governors Inn Hotel Sacramento! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Less than 15 minutes' drive from Sacramento International Airport, this California hotel offers free airport shuttles, an outdoor pool and hot tub. Guest rooms feature free Wi-Fi and cable TV.
Governors Inn Hotel Sacramento provides comfortable rooms with work areas and coffee makers. The spacious studios feature sofa beds.
During their stay, guests can enjoy a coffee, pastry and fruit for breakfast. They can also workout in the hotel's gym and access a business center. Free on-site parking is available.
Sacramento Amtrak, Old Sacramento State Historic Park and the State Capitol Museum are within a 5-minute drive of Sacramento Governors Inn Hotel. Raley Field is 2 miles away.

name: Best Western Sandman Hotel
description:
Located on the Sacramento River, Best Western Sandman Hotel is within 5 minutes' drive of Historic Old Sacramento and the State Capitol. A complimentary hot breakfast is provided.  Guest rooms feature free WiFi.
Every room at Best Western Sandman Hotel includes a mini-fridge and microwave.  Guests can enjoy the cable TV as they relax in the sitting area.  A work desk is also provided.
Omelets, sausage, bacon, pastries, juices. coffees and teas are served daily in the free hot breakfast.  An outdoor pool and hot tub, as well as a fitness center, business center, and guest laundry are available for guests' convenience. Private access to the Sacramento River Trail system offers fishing, bike riding, and hiking. There is access to Discovery Park beach for swimming.
Best Western Sandman Hotel's restaurant, Nina's Mexican Restaurant, serves Mexican cuisine and offers a full bar.

name: Executive Inn & Suites Sacramento
description:
Executive Inn & Suites Sacramento is located within 2 mi of downtown Sacramento and Capitol Park. All rooms include free WiFi and free parking is available.
All rooms are equipped with a microwave, a refrigerator, wet bars, air conditioning and heating, a seating area, ironing facilities, and a TV with satellite and extended film channels.
Business services and a public computer are available in the lobby.
Sacramento City Convention Center and Arco Arena are within 10 minutes' drive away from this hotel. Sacramento Airport is 9 mi away. Guests can walk to the Green Light Rail and Grayhound Bus Station from the Executive Inn & Suites Sacramento.

name: Embassy Suites by Hilton Sacramento Riverfront Promenade
description:
Nestled on the Sacramento River across from historic Old Town Sacramento, Embassy Suites by Hilton Sacramento Riverfront Promenade offers spacious suites with a separate living area. Entertainment venue Golden 1 Center is 10 minutes’ walk away.
The 2-room suites at Embassy Suites by Hilton Sacramento Riverfront Promenade offer two 42-inch flat-screen cable TVs with movie channels. Suites also include a microwave, a refrigerator and a coffee machine.
This hotel serves a cooked-to-order breakfast every morning. For light meals, salads and pizza guests can visit Marketplace Café.
The Crocker Art Museum is 5 minutes’ walk away from the property. The California State Capitol Museum is 1 mi away from Embassy Suites by Hilton Sacramento Riverfront Promenade.

userReviews.title: Comfortable and friendly hotel in the perfect location.
userReviews.positive: The Holiday Inn Sacramento could not be better located.  There is a bus from the airport to the street next to the hotel and the rail station is five minutes away by foot.  The hotel is right next to Old Sacramento which is a cute area of perfectly preserved eighteenth century buildings now occupied by cafes and shops.  My room had a large desk, great chairs and a very comfortable bed.  It also had a bath.  I imagine most people use the shower but it is good to have a bath.  The staff were very friendly and helpful, I really appreciated their support.

name: Inn Off Capitol Park, Ascend Hotel Collection
description:
The Inn Off Capitol Park has rooms with seating areas and work desks as well as a fitness center The hotel is across the street from the California state capitol complex.
Rooms at the Inn Off Capitol Park, an Ascend Collection Hotel, offer free cable on flat-screen TVs. Guests will find microwaves and refrigerators, coffee makers and ironing facilities. Some rooms also have seating areas with sofas.
There’s a business center in the hotel, with free Wi-Fi and wired Internet access available throughout. The atrium lobby offers comfortable seating and casual conversation areas.
One block from the State Capitol and Museum, the hotel is less than a mile from the Sacramento Convention Center. Old Sacramento State Historic Park is 2 miles from the Inn Off Capitol Park, and the Sacramento Zoo is 3 miles away.

name: Delta King Hotel
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Delta King Hotel! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Conveniently located in Sacramento, Delta King Hotel provides air-conditioned rooms, a restaurant, free WiFi and a bar. The property is close to several well-known attractions, a 19-minute walk from California Capitol Building, 900 feet from California State Railroad Museum and 1.2 miles from California State Capitol and Museum. The hotel has a sun terrace and a 24-hour front desk.
Each room is equipped with a flat-screen TV, and certain rooms at the hotel have a city view. Guest rooms in Delta King Hotel are equipped with free toiletries and a computer.
A continental breakfast is available daily at the accommodation.
Guests at Delta King Hotel will be able to enjoy activities in and around Sacramento, like cycling.
Popular points of interest near the hotel include Crocker Art Museum, Raley Field and Sacramento Valley Amtrak Station. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 10 miles from Delta King Hotel.

name: Econo Lodge Sacramento Convention Center
description:
The Econo Lodge is conveniently located in downtown, blocks from the Sacramento Convention Center and less than two miles from historic Old Town Sacramento. This Sacramento hotel is close to area attractions including the California Exposition and State Fairgrounds, California State University, the California State Capitol, the Sacramento Zoo and the Governor's Mansion.
This Sacramento hotel also offers connecting rooms and Suites. In addition to standard amenities, all guest rooms come with irons and ironing boards. Some rooms come equipped with refrigerators.
The Sacramento International Airport is only 15 miles from the hotel. There are a wide variety of restaurants and cocktail lounges located in the area. Visitors will enjoy shopping at the nearby Arden Way Mall.
Full-service hotel accommodations and features include: Free continental breakfast; Free coffee; Pet-friendly hotel; Fax services; Tour bus parking
There is a newsstand located on the property. Handicap accessible and nonsmoking rooms are also available. Pets are welcome with a small nightly fee.

name: The Exchange Sacramento, Curio Collection By Hilton
description:
Featuring a fitness center, a restaurant as well as a bar, The Exchange Sacramento, Curio Collection By Hilton is located in the center of Sacramento, 17 miles from University of California, Davis. This 4-star hotel offers room service, a 24-hour front desk and free WiFi. The property has a concierge service and luggage storage space for guests.
The hotel will provide guests with air-conditioned rooms with a desk, a coffee machine, a fridge, a safety deposit box, a flat-screen TV and a private bathroom with a shower. At The Exchange Sacramento, Curio Collection By Hilton rooms include bed linen and towels.
Continental and Italian breakfast options are available each morning at the accommodation.
Guests can use the business center or relax in the snack bar.
Popular points of interest near The Exchange Sacramento, Curio Collection By Hilton include Sacramento Valley Amtrak Station, California State Railroad Museum and California Capitol Building. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 9.3 miles from the hotel.

name: Kimpton Sawyer Hotel, an IHG Hotel
description:
Offering a year-round outdoor pool, Kimpton Sawyer Hotel is located in the heart of Sacramento at the Downtown Commons (DOCO).  The hotel offers private parking a variety of on-site dining options. The California State Railroad Museum is 1,950 feet away.
A flat-screen TV with cable channels are featured. Certain units include a seating area to relax in after a busy day. Rooms have a private bathroom. Extras include bathrobes and free toiletries. Some rooms include views. Keurig or Nespresso coffee machines are available upon request.
The pool-level lounge, Revival at the Sawyer, offers unique cocktails and bar bites for guests.
Guests can also dine at Echo & Rig, which is a steakhouse that offers lunch & dinner at the hotel. Punch Bowl Social offers lunch, and dinner in a casual atmosphere with a curated list of cocktails, beer, and wine.
There is a 24-hour front desk at the property. The hotel has a terrace and a fitness center. The hotel also offers free use of bicycles.
California Capitol Building is 2,300 feet from Kimpton Sawyer Hotel, while California State Capitol and Museum is 2,650 feet from the property. Sacramento Airport is 9.3 mi away.

It was Difficult to get service but eventually got drinks and food but I gave up on getting napkins and utensils and used my fingers so my friend could use the one set of chopsticks provided IN the food. We clock watched waiting for Revival to open and got great and friendly service even though we only got drinks. I would love it if at least the bar had been open earlier so we could have avoided the Punchbowl. Definitely Not going there for anything again. Echo & Rig was fabulous and I would stay at Kimpton-Sawyer again just for that dining experience. name: Hyatt Regency Sacramento
description:
Located across the street from the California State Capitol, Hyatt Regency Sacramento features an outdoor heated pool, a restaurant, and a full service spa. Free WiFi is offered in all rooms.
Subtle gold, red and white accents are featured in every contemporary, spacious room. A flat-screen TV, a coffee machine, and free toiletries in the private bathroom is offered.
Outdoor fireplace, high ceilings, soft gray décor, an illuminated bar and modern chandeliers are featured at Dawson's Steakhouse, the restaurant located onsite. Vines Café features serves Northern California cuisine for breakfast and lunch.
A Starbucks Coffee bar, a 24-hour fitness center, dry cleaning services and massage services are all onsite. A gift shop is also available.
Sacramento International Airport is 20 minutes’ drive away. Sacramento Convention Center Complex is just 5 minutes’ walk away from Hyatt Regency Sacramento.

name: Sterling Hotel
description:
Attractively set in the center of Sacramento, Sterling Hotel has air-conditioned rooms, a shared lounge, free WiFi and a terrace. The property is located 17 miles from University of California, Davis, a 11-minute walk from California Capitol Building and one mile from California State Railroad Museum. Guests can use the hot tub, or enjoy city views.
At the hotel, rooms have a desk, a flat-screen TV, a private bathroom, bed linen and towels. The rooms will provide guests with a fridge.
Popular points of interest near Sterling Hotel include Sacramento Convention Center, California State Capitol and Museum and Sacramento Valley Amtrak Station. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 9.3 miles from the accommodation.

name: Sheraton Grand Sacramento
description:
Located inside the beautifully restored Public Market Building, this Sacramento hotel is near area points of interest and provides comfortable accommodations and modern amenities, in the heart of the city.
Guests can then enjoy a restful night's sleep on the hotel's signature Sweet Sleeper beds. Offering air conditioning, all rooms include a safety deposit box, a flat-screen TV with cable channels, a coffee machine, a work desk, and an private bathroom with a hairdryer, a bathrobe, and free toiletries.
After a long day in the city, guests at the Sheraton Sacramento can have a delicious meal at one of the 3 on-site restaurants or relax in the outdoor swimming pool.
The Sheraton Grand Sacramento is ideally located across from the Sacramento Convention Center and is only one block from the state Capitol building. A number of museums, golf courses, restaurants and shopping centers can also be found nearby.

userReviews.title: Enjoyable stay near the mall
userReviews.positive: Check-in process was fast and efficient.  Amazing location.  We walked to the Arden fair mall, and could walk to a hundred different restaurants.  The room was large and comfortable and smelled fresh and clean.  All of the staff were very friendly and accomodating.  The bed and pillows were comfortable. There was a nice ironing board, and a safe. The free breakfast buffet had a great variety.  The outdoor hot tub had great bubbles and jets, and was nice and hot.  The gym had nice treadmills and an elliptical machine, free weights, and more.  There were signs in the hallway making it easy to find the room, gym, ice machine, etc.
userReviews.negative: We had to walk to the front desk to get hot tub towels, but it was winter so maybe they can't leave them out due to rain.  Also, the table and couch in the living room area was dirty and could use some refreshing.  The lighting could've been better by the bed.  The front desk was great about giving us change for the washer and dryer, but a change machine next to the machines would have been nice.  Also, the water pressure was weak in the shower and the shampoo dispenser took forever to dispense. The decaf coffee in the room was very bad.  I also thought it was odd that the hotel guide in the room, listing the hours for breakfast, pool hours, checkout time, etc, had a different hotel name on it -- Lexington was their former name, but it had been changed years ago.  Perhaps an update would be good.  Overall, though, we were quite pleased with the stay and the location.
userReviews.room: Deluxe Room with Two Queen Beds - Non-Smoking

Located 1.5 miles from Raging Waters Sacramento, Residence Inn Sacramento Cal Expo features suites with full kitchens and free Wi-Fi. It has a heated outdoor pool, a hot tub and gym.
The spacious suites offer flat-screen TVs with HBO and first-nighter kits. They provide sofa beds, sitting areas and desks and are also equipped with ironing facilities and hairdryers.
Residence Inn Sacramento serves a breakfast buffet. It has a picnic area and offers grocery shopping services. A meeting room is available.
Residence Inn is one mile from the Cal Expo and 2 miles from Arden Fair Mall. It is 4 miles from Sutter's Fort State Historic Park and 8 miles from Fairytale Town and Sacramento Zoo.

name: TownePlace Suites Sacramento Airport Natomas
description:
TownePlace Suites Sacramento Airport Natomas is a sustainable condo hotel in Sacramento where guests can make the most of its outdoor swimming pool, fitness center, and free bikes. This 3-star condo hotel offers free shuttle service and a 24-hour front desk. There's a sun terrace and guests can make use of free Wifi, free private parking, and an an electric vehicle charging station.
At the condo hotel, the units come with a wardrobe. Every room has a coffee machine and a private bathroom with a shower and a hair dryer, while certain rooms include a fully equipped kitchen. At the condo hotel, every unit has bed linen and towels.
Guests at the condo hotel can enjoy an American breakfast. There is a snack bar, and a mini-market is also available.
The area is popular for cycling and hiking, and car rental is available at this 3-star condo hotel. With an outdoor fireplace and a picnic area, this condo hotel offers plenty of opportunities to relax.
University of California, Davis is 20 miles from TownePlace Suites Sacramento Airport Natomas, while Discovery Park is 4.5 miles away. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 5 miles from the accommodation.

userReviews.title: Nice facility, terrible policy on transport to and from the airport, saved by very considerate clerk
userReviews.positive: The facility is new and modern, so very clean and the rooms are large. The desk clerk who checked me in was very friendly and helpful.
userReviews.negative: The main reason I chose this hotel was because they have a free transportation system whereby taxis will take you to and from the airport for free. I mentioned this to the clerk when I said I needed an early taxi for my early flight. She looked unhappy and said that it didn't operate on weekends. I was extremely upset. She said that it says this later on in the small print. She was sympathetic to me and said she had told the hotel management that it was wrong not to mention the complete policy when first describing the deal. I wanted to drop the car off at the car rental area and then take a taxi back to the hotel and then to the airport the next day because I'd read that the bus between the car rental center and the airport wasn't reliable. The cost of the taxi was $30 with tip, so that was an extra $60 to the cost of the hotel. When I returned to the hotel after dropping my rental off, I told the same clerk about the cost and she said that she would comp me the taxi cost the next morning. Sure enough, she did and I want to thank her so much. I won't mention her name just in case she might get in trouble for going against the hotel policy, but it was so nice to see someone who took the customer's side over the hotel's side. Thank you again!

name: Hampton Inn & Suites Sacramento at CSUS
description:
Featuring 3-star accommodations, Hampton Inn & Suites Sacramento at CSUS is located in Sacramento, 21 miles from University of California, Davis and a 18-minute walk from California State University, Sacramento. With an outdoor swimming pool, the 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. Private parking is available on site.
At the hotel, every room comes with a desk and a flat-screen TV. At Hampton Inn & Suites Sacramento at CSUS rooms contain bed linen and towels.
Breakfast is available each morning, and includes buffet, continental and American options.
Guests can use the business center, work out at the gym or relax in the snack bar. Speaking Arabic, English and Spanish, staff are willing to help at any time of the day at the reception.
Punch Line Sacramento is 4.1 miles from the accommodation, while California State Capitol and Museum is 4.8 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 15 miles from Hampton Inn & Suites Sacramento at CSUS.

name: Larkspur Landing Sacramento-An All-Suite Hotel
description:
This Sacramento hotel is 5 minutes' drive from California State University and Raging Waters Water Park. It features modern all-suite accommodations with a kitchenette.
A flat-screen cable TV, DVD player and iPod docking stations are some of the standard items in each suite at Larkspur Landing Sacramento-An All-Suite Hotel. All suites include air conditioning and a large work desk.
Freshly baked cookies and free coffee are offered each day in the lobby.
Free access to the on-site gym and business center is provided to all guests of Sacramento Larkspur Landing. The library offers books and DVDs to borrow.
Parking is free and Sacramento International Airport is a 30-minute drive from the hotel. Crocker Art Museum and the Sacramento Zoo are both 8 miles away.

name: Extended Stay America Suites - Sacramento - Northgate
description:
This Extended Stay America - Sacramento - Northgate is located in Sacramento and especially designed for longer stays, with all rooms featuring a fully equipped kitchen. The hotel offers free WiFi and a 24-hour front desk.
Every kitchen at Extended Stay America - Sacramento - Northgate is equipped with a stovetop, microwave and a fridge. The hotel also provides guests with laundry and ironing facilities, and upgraded bedding with extra pillows in every room.
Free grab-and-go breakfast including breakfast bars, muffins, hot cereal, coffee and tea is served every morning.
Free weekly housekeeping services are provided and towels and linen can be exchanged at the front desk.
The property offers free onsite parking. Attractions within close proximity to the hotel include the CA State Capitol Building, the Raging Water Park and the Power Balance Pavilion.

description:

Offering patios and riverfront views, Scott’s Seafood restaurant is located on-site at the Sacramento Westin. Serving breakfast, lunch and dinner, the restaurant offers four-star quality food. Room service is available.
William Land Park Golf Course is 5-minutes’ drive from the The Westin Sacramento and the California State Capitol Building is 4 miles away.

The only issue I have with Westin is I booked my hotel through Booking.com where it states NOTHING about mandatory Valet which is posted at Westin.
 In fact, it states valet as optional on the site. Being forced to pay 135.00 in valet fees wasn't within my budget nor was I told I would be charged either by booking.com NOR by Westin. 
Even though the staff was absolutely amazing and naturally it would be presumed a fee for service would be required and these young men deserve the money. I just feel if you are going to demand I use this service then charge me for it, then, I should be told by both  booking.com AND at Westin. I truly felt I should have the option to choose this service nor given the surprise to the added charges.

name: Hilton Sacramento Arden West
description:
In the Point West Business District of Sacramento, this hotel offers a great location near a variety of attractions as well as spacious guest rooms.
Hilton Sacramento Arden West provides convenient access to the Cal Expo, home of the California State Fair. The California State Capitol, historic Old Sacramento and the Sacramento Convention Center are just a short drive away. Guests will appreciate the hotel's free transportation to the nearby Arden Fair Mall, which has 165 stores.
After a busy day of exploring, guests can relax in a guest room with comfortable beds and luxurious linens. Guests can watch an On Demand movie on the 35-inch flat-screen TV or listen to the alarm clock with MP3 compatibility.

name: DoubleTree By Hilton Sacramento
description:
Placed on 17 acres just off the Capital City Freeway motorway, this hotel is located in Sacramento's Arden-Point West Business District. It features a restaurant and rooms with balconies.
DoubleTree By Hilton Sacramento offers rooms and suites with comfortable seating areas, desks and cable TV. They also include tea/coffee-making facilities.
Facilities include an outdoor pool, 24-hour gym and business center. Guests can grab take out at Twigs Cafe or have a drink at Twigs Lounge with limited hours
Sacramento DoubleTree is 1 miles from Riverfront Park and 3 miles from California State University - Sacramento. It is 12 miles from Sacramento International Airport.

description:
TownPlace Suites Sacramento is next to the Cal Expo and Interstate 80.  It offers a outdoor pool and rooms with LCD TVs and well-equipped kitchens. Free WiFi is provided.

 A daily complimentary hot breakfast is available to guests each morning. The Market at TownePlace Suites Cal Expo stocks a selection of snacks and beverages.  BBQ facilities are also available on site.
The American River Parkway and Arden Fair are 10 minutes’ walk away.  Sacramento International Airport is 12 mi from TownPlace Suites Sacramento.

userReviews.title: Clean rooms and Friendly staff, but the guests were something else
userReviews.positive: The staff were friendly. The rooms were clean. The landscape was clean. Easy access location. They are pet friendly which was a plus for me.
userReviews.negative: I had requested a late check-in but they nearly gave my rooms away because they were overbooked.  I had to plead with them to give me my rooms.  When I pulled into the parking lot, there were several young kids (under the age of 9) roaming the parking lots unsupervised and running in front of cars.  I told the on-site security guard and he said they've been told multiple times.  As I dove to my room, another guest was in the middle of the parking lot drawling cartoon characters with chalk for the other 10 minors outside watching him at 10:45 pm.  I literally had to wait for him to stop drawling before I could proceed to my room. As I was unpacking my car to head to my room, I was approached by a creepy guest in the parking lot asking me if I wanted a drink (he was reaching into the trunk of his car with red plastic cups). Thankfully, I had my dog with me as I did not feel comfortable walking to my room alone. Inside the room, the smoke detector was disabled in one room (laying on the dresser).  There were no knobs to turn on the stove top. Several of the brackets on the closet shelves were loose and coming off the walls. Needless to say, I will not be staying there again. I truly did not feel safe.

userReviews.title: Downgraded Room
userReviews.positive: When I first tried to check in, my card was declined because my bank marked it as suspicious activity, however, I went outside and corrected it within 5 minutes. When I came back to check in again, the second desk clerk charged me a significantly cheaper price and once we checked into the room I realized it was downgraded. I’m not sure why two separate people charged me a $175 difference if my room was not downgraded and if so, what is the reason for the price difference? This trip was supposed to be a special occasion for my husband’s birthday and we were extremely underwhelmed. The windows were not sound proof either so you could hear all the homeless people screaming throughout the night. The small room we got was clean however. We probably will not be staying here again.

name: Hilton Garden Inn Sacramento/South Natomas
description:
Located 10 minutes' drive north of downtown Sacramento and the California State Capitol, the Hilton Garden Inn Sacramento features a restaurant, an outdoor pool and rooms with a 32-inch flat-screen TV.
All rooms include a microwave, a refrigerator, and a coffee machine. A spacious work desk, free WiFi and designer toiletries are also provided.
Hilton Garden Inn Sacramento features a fitness center, an outdoor hot tub, and a 24-hour business center. Laundry facilities are on site. Complimentary SMF shuttles are available from 5:00 until 22:00 daily.
The Garden Grille and Bar is open for breakfast and dinner, along with room service. Drinks are served at the Pavilion Lounge and guests can get snacks from the Pavilion Pantry 24 hours.
Discovery Park is 5 minutes' drive from this Garden Hilton Inn. ARCO Arena and Sutter's Fort are just 10 minutes' drive away.

name: SpringHill Suites by Marriott Sacramento Natomas
description:
Located 18 miles from University of California, Davis, SpringHill Suites by Marriott Sacramento Natomas offers 3-star accommodations in Sacramento and has free bikes, a fitness center and a shared lounge. This 3-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk, a business center and free WiFi. Guests can have a drink at the snack bar.
Some rooms also feature a kitchenette with a fridge and a microwave.
Guests at the hotel can enjoy a continental breakfast.
Discovery Park is 1.9 miles from SpringHill Suites by Marriott Sacramento Natomas, while California State Railroad Museum is 2.8 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 8.7 miles from the accommodation.

name: La Quinta Inn by Wyndham Sacramento North
description:
Just 1 miles away from American River College, this Sacramento hotel features an outdoor pool and hot tub. Each room offers free Wi-Fi. A daily continental breakfast is included.
Boasting a flat-screen HD cable TV with premium channels, the rooms at La Quinta Inn Sacramento North are equipped with a seating area and desk.
A guest launderette is located on-site at the pet-friendly North Sacramento La Quinta Inn. A free newspaper is provided.
The Cal Expo and the California State Railroad Museum are all within 10 miles of the hotel. The California State Capitol is 15 minutes’ drive from the La Quinta Inn Sacramento North.

name: Wyndham Sacramento
description:
Wyndham Sacramento in Sacramento has 3-star accommodations with a fitness center and a restaurant. With an outdoor swimming pool, the 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. The property is non-smoking throughout and is located 27 miles from University of California, Davis.
At the hotel rooms come with a closet and a flat-screen TV.
Guests at Wyndham Sacramento can enjoy a continental breakfast.
Speaking English, Spanish, Hindi and Russian at the 24-hour front desk, staff are always at hand to help.
Punch Line Sacramento is 7.9 miles from the accommodation, while Discovery Park is 10 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Sacramento International Airport, 16 miles from Wyndham Sacramento.

userReviews.negative:
There was no restaurant or room service.
The room I was given was way too far from the 
front desk to the room for an elderly person. 
There was an adjoining room…no thanks!
The carpet looked old.
There was no closet for hanging up clothes, just a bar with hangers which was too low to the ground to hang up a dress.
The door did not feel fit to the size of the entrance
The dead bolt and swinging lock bar seemed too small for the door
The freeway was outside my window and was extremely loud all night long
There were large trucks in the parking lot at 6:30a that were loudly beeping as if they were backing up (might have been garbage trucks)
This is my first stay at this hotel since Wyndham bought the property.  I was extremely disappointed that Wyndham did not have the same quality front desk help.  The room was only just adequate, but the location of the room was terrible.  There was no door sign to prevent the maid from banging on the door in the morning.   It was the worst room I was ever given in that hotel.  I had at least 10 stays at this hotel when it was Crown Plaza.  They always upgraded me if they had an available room. This new ownership changed the quality of the stay.  On a scale of 1-5, The Crown Plaza was a 4.5.  This Wyndham property I would rate at just adequate, a 3.

name: Four Points by Sheraton Sacramento Airport
description:

description:
Ideally located just minutes from downtown Sacramento and the Sacramento International Airport, this comfortable hotel offers convenient amenities near a variety of attractions and recreational activities.
All guest rooms offer a TV with on-demand movies and cable channels, a refrigerator, a microwave, a coffee machine, and an private bathroom. Select rooms include a sofa bed.
Guests will enjoy free amenities such as high-speed internet access and a daily continental breakfast at the Sacramento Hampton Inn. The hotel's fitness room and outdoor heated pool are great places for guests to relax after a long day.
Hampton Inn & Suites Sacramento features a great location near shopping and dining as well as the city's vibrant arts scene. Guests can explore the California State Capitol, the Discovery Museum of Sacramento and the Sacramento Zoo easily from the hotel. The nearby Sacramento River is great for activities such as hiking, fishing, boating and more.

name: Comfort Inn & Suites Sacramento – University Area
description:
Comfort Inn & Suites Sacramento - University Area is conveniently located 15 minutes from the Sacramento International Airport and 7 miles from downtown. It has guest accommodations with free Wi-Fi and an indoor heated pool.
All spacious rooms and suites at this hotel feature microwaves, refrigerators, hairdryers, coffee makers, irons and ironing boards. All suites feature minibars and separate sitting areas with sofa sleepers. Free local calls are also included. Select suites also include relaxing spa tubs.
Guests at Comfort Inn & Suites Sacramento - University Area are provided a daily free hot breakfast featuring eggs, meat, yogurt and fresh fruit, cereal and a choice of hot waffle flavors. Free coffee is available in the lobby.
Free well-lit parking is available. Guests can also enjoy the exercise room and the hot tub. Laundry facilities are on site. Free newspapers are available.
This Sacramento, CA hotel's ideal location has easy access to highways, businesses and attractions like Old Sacramento, the Sacramento Zoo, Crocker Art Museum and California State University, Sacramento. Additional area points of interest close to this California hotel include the California State Capitol Building and Six Flags Waterworld USA.

description:

A cable TV with premium film channels and a work desk are provided in each room at this hotel. Featuring a bath or shower, private bathrooms include free toiletries.
At Rodeway Inn Sacramento-University Area you will find a 24-hour front desk. Other facilities offered at the property include laundry facilities and a vending machine featuring cold beverages. The property offers free parking.
Sacramento Airport is located 14 mi away from this hotel.

name: Hilton Garden Inn Sacramento Airport Natomas
description:
Located in Sacramento, Hilton Garden Inn Sacramento Airport Natomas offers free WiFi. With a fitness center, the property also has a shared lounge. A complimentary airport shuttle is provided.
All guest rooms in the hotel are equipped with a flat-screen TV. A refrigerator, microwave and a coffee maker are provided as well. The private bathroom is fitted with a shower and a hair dryer. The rooms include a seating area.
An American Breakfast is served daily at the property. Hilton Garden Inn Sacramento Airport Natomas offers an outdoor pool. Staff at the 24-hour front desk can help guests with any queries that they may have. An on-site restaurant and bar are available.
Crocker Art Museum is 6.8 mi from the accommodations, while California Capitol Building is 6.8 mi from the property. Sacramento Airport is 6.2 mi away.

userReviews.title: The hotel was absolutely top notch. I would recommend it without hesitation.
userReviews.positive: What we liked the most was the security of the hotel. We stayed in a hotel the last time we were in Sacramento and there were homeless people wandering around in the parking lot, some were deranged. At that hotel we had to go out of the lobby to get to our room. At the Natomas Hilton everything was enclosed; there was no outside access to our room. We ate at the restaurant which was located in the lobby. We had breakfast and dinner, and both were very good--especially the dinner special, steak and shrimp--delicious! The room was very nice--we stayed in a room that was designed for wheelchair access, and it was very spacious. The thermostat was simple and it was easy to control the room temperature. The room and the bathroom were very clean. We will definitely be staying here next time we come to Sacramento!
userReviews.negative: The refrigerator in the room stopped working on the second day we were there. That is really the only negative thing I have to say about our stay. We were going to check out in a few hours so we didn't ask for it to be looked at. We informed the desk when we checked out.

userReviews.title: Enjoyed
userReviews.positive: The shower set up was different, I liked.
userReviews.negative: Not enough parking onsite, having to use the “overflow “ parking. At night walking alone was a bit scary.
userReviews.room: Queen Room with Two Queen Beds

name: Motel 6-Sacramento, CA - Central
description:
Featuring an outdoor pool, this motel is 2 miles from California State University, Sacramento.  It features rooms that include a cable TV with extended channels and Free Wifi.  Laundry facilities is also located on site.
Each air-conditioned room at Motel 6 Sacramento Central features an private bathroom. All rooms boast vibrant décor and light wood furnishings.
Sacramento Central Motel 6 offers 24-hour reception. Fax and photocopying services are available.
Arden Fair Shopping Center is 4 miles from this motel. Sacramento Convention is 10 minutes’ drive away.  Thunder Valley Casino is 30 miles away.
